text: Ozerki () is a rural locality (a village) in Staroarzamatovsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 226 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 11 km from Mishkino, 4 km from Malonakaryakovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Ozerki, Mishkinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
